  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Tracheostomy is worldwide used for critically ill patients. The aim of our study is to assess
      the mortality, quality of life, laryngeal function, procedures, early and late complications
      of tracheostomy performed for critically ill patients admitted in intensive care units.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
